1-FINAL Keyword
final is a keyword used to restrict modification. It can be applied to variables, methods, and classes.
There are 3 main uses of final:

Final Variable
Final Method
Final Class


1. Final Variable ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Definition
A final variable can be assigned only once.
Once a value is assigned, it cannot be changed.

2. Final Method ⭐⭐⭐⭐
A final method cannot be overridden.
Parent
class Animal {
    final void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal Sound");
    }
}
Child
class Dog extends Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Dog");
    }
}
Output
Compile Error


3. Final Class ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
A final class cannot be inherited.
Example
final class Animal {

}
Now
class Dog extends Animal {

}
Compile Error.
